true colors the chemistry of art materials arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe featured archive gallery true colors the chemistry of art materials a student a professor an artist and a curator teamed up to create an exhibition at the cantor arts center that explored the chemistry of art materials chemical engineering professor curt frank artist sara loesch frank student ivy nguyen class of 2013 and susan roberts manganelli manager of collections exhibitions and conservation at cantor arts center collaborated to create true colors an exhibition at the cantor arts center that opened march 16 2011 nguyen served as the student curator leading a team that used x ray fluorescence to find traces of pigment on a greco roman statuary in the cantor arts center's collection the project was an outgrowth of frank and loesch frank's popular sophomore seminar course in chemical engineering art chemistry and madness the science of art materials for which roberts manganelli has also contributed cantor arts center jonathan poto sica photographer 2010 2011 home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
